A vintage-style illustration of a wooden drafting desk viewed from above, covered with scattered flowcharts, organizational diagrams, and mind maps drawn on cream-colored paper. Colored pencils, a brass compass, and a wooden ruler rest among the papers. The diagrams feature interconnected geometric shapes in muted teal, coral, and mustard yellow, with organic branching lines resembling tree roots connecting various nodes. Warm afternoon sunlight streams across the desk from a nearby window, casting long shadows and giving the scene a nostalgic 1970s technical illustration feel. The paper has slightly yellowed edges and the pencils show signs of use, conveying the satisfaction of visual thinking and the craft of turning complex ideas into clear pictures.
